  "prompt": "What does \u597d\u840c\u963f mean?",
  "response": "\"\u597d\u840c\u554a\" (h\u01ceo m\u00e9ng a) is a phrase commonly used in Chinese to describe something or someone as \"very cute\" or \"adorable.\" The word \"\u840c\" (m\u00e9ng) itself originates from Japanese, where it is used to describe something or someone that is charming, endearing, or cute in a way that evokes affection. \n\nWhen someone says \"\u597d\u840c\u554a,\" they are expressing admiration or affection for the cuteness of an object, animal, or person. This phrase is often used in casual conversations, especially among younger people or fans of anime, manga, and other forms of pop culture.",
